00:59:29.308 --> 00:59:32.928
The prototype for T-cell engagers was really blinatumomab.

987
00:59:33.448 --> 00:59:37.328
It was the first bispecific T-cell engager to be approved.

988
00:59:37.648 --> 00:59:41.608
It targets CD19, and it's approved in acute lymphoblastic

989
00:59:41.668 --> 00:59:42.348
leukemia.

990
00:59:43.548 --> 00:59:46.888
By making some protein engineering changes, we could extend the

991
00:59:46.928 --> 00:59:50.488
half-life, and talatinib is a molecule that targets

992
00:59:50.548 --> 00:59:54.108
DLL3 and has been approved for small cell lung

993
00:59:54.188 --> 00:59:54.628
cancer.

994
00:59:56.328 --> 00:59:59.848
To try to bring molecules into other settings,

995
01:00:00.448 --> 01:00:02.608
we've used an avidity-based approach.

996
01:00:02.888 --> 01:00:06.748
We call that two plus one binding, and the molecule I'll highlight for

997
01:00:06.848 --> 01:00:10.128
you is now called zalyutamig, and it's being

998
01:00:10.908 --> 01:00:13.248
used to treat patients with prostate cancer.

999
01:00:14.888 --> 01:00:18.708
And finally, I'll tell you about an exciting novel approach that

1000
01:00:18.788 --> 01:00:22.248
we refer to as dual targeting, where we use two

1001
01:00:22.468 --> 01:00:26.288
receptors to increase the therapeutic window and

1002
01:00:26.348 --> 01:00:28.308
move into additional indications.

1003
01:00:32.588 --> 01:00:36.148
So unfortunately, cancer remains the second leading

1004
01:00:36.288 --> 01:00:40.204
cause of death worldwide.We've been making some

1005
01:00:40.364 --> 01:00:43.924
great progress in the field over the past several decades,

1006
01:00:44.384 --> 01:00:48.244
much of which you've heard about from my co-presenters today

1007
01:00:48.564 --> 01:00:49.914
and throughout this meeting.

1008
01:00:51.454 --> 01:00:54.044
The graph that you're looking at on the right-hand side

1009
01:00:54.944 --> 01:00:57.344
shows the five-year survival percentage,

1010
01:00:58.164 --> 01:01:01.204
and in some indications, we've made tremendous progress.

1011
01:01:02.324 --> 01:01:05.404
The indications at the top of the slide, like melanoma,

1012
01:01:06.004 --> 01:01:09.544
prostate cancer, and breast, we're now in the 90%

1013
01:01:09.664 --> 01:01:12.004
range, which is truly remarkable.

1014
01:01:12.924 --> 01:01:16.864
But some of the indications at the bottom of the slide, we haven't been able

1015
01:01:16.964 --> 01:01:18.704
to make so much progress yet.

1016
01:01:21.024 --> 01:01:24.644
Immunotherapy has really been a revolution in the field.

1017
01:01:25.904 --> 01:01:29.264
And since the first wave of immunotherapy, the checkpoint

1018
01:01:29.324 --> 01:01:32.913
inhibitors were approved way back in 2011 and

1019
01:01:33.044 --> 01:01:37.014
2014. They've had a large impact on some of

1020
01:01:37.084 --> 01:01:38.344
these indications.

1021
01:01:39.864 --> 01:01:43.464
But still, it remains true that most patients don't derive

1022
01:01:43.504 --> 01:01:45.184
benefit from immunotherapy.

1023
01:01:46.174 --> 01:01:49.304
And so that's where T-cell engagers step up.

1024
01:01:52.764 --> 01:01:56.424
A T-cell engager is a targeted form of immunotherapy.

1025
01:01:58.224 --> 01:02:01.524
And the way it works is they're usually bispecific antibodies.

1026
01:02:01.644 --> 01:02:05.604
They have two arms. One arm binds to CD3 on a

1027
01:02:05.664 --> 01:02:09.124
T-cell, and the other arm binds to a

1028
01:02:09.184 --> 01:02:10.604
tumor-selective antigen.

1029
01:02:11.924 --> 01:02:15.834
By bringing the T-cell into close proximity with the tumor cell,

1030
01:02:16.364 --> 01:02:20.344
it results in the very specific and potent cell killing

1031
01:02:20.424 --> 01:02:21.584
of the tumor cells.

1032
01:02:23.464 --> 01:02:27.444
The T-cells become activated, and they go on to proliferate

1033
01:02:27.584 --> 01:02:29.404
and kill more tumor cells.

1034
01:02:31.424 --> 01:02:34.684
We found this to be one of the most potent mechanisms of cell

1035
01:02:34.784 --> 01:02:36.504
killing that we've looked at.

1036
01:02:38.344 --> 01:02:41.784
So as I mentioned, blinatumomab was the first T-cell

1037
01:02:41.844 --> 01:02:43.464
engager to be approved.

1038
01:02:44.364 --> 01:02:48.324
In this case, the structure of the molecule is shown on the left-hand side of the

1039
01:02:48.384 --> 01:02:51.784
slide, and it binds to CD19, which is

1040
01:02:51.864 --> 01:02:53.924
expressed on malignant B-cells.

1041
01:02:56.864 --> 01:03:00.764
The sections on the right-hand side of the slide come from a lymphoma

1042
01:03:00.864 --> 01:03:03.264
patient that was treated with blinatumomab.

1043
01:03:04.824 --> 01:03:08.624
And what you're looking at in the top two panels are bone marrow

1044
01:03:08.744 --> 01:03:12.724
sections that have been stained for either

1045
01:03:12.764 --> 01:03:15.144
malignant B-cells or T-cells.

1046
01:03:16.364 --> 01:03:20.064
After just 15 days of treatment, you can see that

1047
01:03:20.124 --> 01:03:23.504
most of the tumor cells have been eradicated and the

1048
01:03:23.544 --> 01:03:27.004
T-cells have expanded, very much in line with the

1049
01:03:27.044 --> 01:03:28.724
mechanism I just described.

1050
01:03:30.164 --> 01:03:32.744
And in the lower panel, you're looking at liver

1051
01:03:33.364 --> 01:03:37.104
biopsies from, again, a patient treated with blincyto.

1052
01:03:37.124 --> 01:03:41.024
In this case, the patient was treated for three weeks, but you

1053
01:03:41.064 --> 01:03:44.294
can see that the B-cells have been almost entirely

1054
01:03:44.344 --> 01:03:46.384
eradicated from the liver.

1055
01:03:51.704 --> 01:03:55.574
So I think this study really highlights the power of

1056
01:03:55.584 --> 01:03:56.784
T-cell engagers.

1057
01:03:58.114 --> 01:04:01.444
This was a clinical study that was run in acute lymphoblastic

1058
01:04:01.504 --> 01:04:02.184
leukemia,

1059
01:04:03.064 --> 01:04:06.824
and what the investigators did after the patients had been

1060
01:04:06.904 --> 01:04:10.504
treated with chemotherapy, they randomized them into two

1061
01:04:10.624 --> 01:04:11.624
treatment arms.

1062
01:04:12.784 --> 01:04:16.124
These patients were MRD negative at the time,

1063
01:04:17.244 --> 01:04:19.034
minimal residual disease negative.

1064
01:04:19.124 --> 01:04:21.244
There is no detectable disease.

1065
01:04:22.324 --> 01:04:25.904
And then they followed these patients for over five

1066
01:04:26.004 --> 01:04:26.524
years.

1067
01:04:27.924 --> 01:04:31.624
And you can see that the patients that received blinatumomab

1068
01:04:31.644 --> 01:04:35.534
plus chemotherapy do significantly better than

1069
01:04:35.564 --> 01:04:39.124
the patients that just received chemotherapy alone.

1070
01:04:40.264 --> 01:04:43.904
I should say that these patients only received four cycles of

1071
01:04:43.944 --> 01:04:47.864
treatment, and so it really shows the power of

1072
01:04:47.884 --> 01:04:51.384
T-cell engagers in developing a

1073
01:04:51.504 --> 01:04:53.084
safe and durable

1074
01:04:54.084 --> 01:04:54.784
response.

1075
01:04:55.603 --> 01:04:59.434
So I think these are really exciting data, and I hope we can go on

1076
01:04:59.484 --> 01:05:02.884
to see other data like this in other indications.

1077
01:05:07.404 --> 01:05:11.384
So since the approval of blinatumomab in 2014,

1078
01:05:11.924 --> 01:05:15.884
nine other T-cell engagers have been approved by the FDA,

1079
01:05:17.004 --> 01:05:18.744
and they're listed on this slide here.

1080
01:05:19.524 --> 01:05:23.424
You can see the molecule names, the target that they go after, the

1081
01:05:23.484 --> 01:05:26.104
format, and the approved indication.

1082
01:05:28.224 --> 01:05:31.924
The vast majority of these T-cell engagers have been approved in

1083
01:05:31.964 --> 01:05:33.804
hematologic malignancies.

1084
01:05:34.844 --> 01:05:38.304
Only two of them have been approved in the solid tumor setting,

1085
01:05:39.104 --> 01:05:43.024
and that is kimmtrak, which targets GP100

1086
01:05:43.044 --> 01:05:45.144
and was approved in uveal melanoma,

1087
01:05:46.034 --> 01:05:49.664
and more recently, talatrimab or imdeltrac, which

1088
01:05:49.724 --> 01:05:53.684
targets DLL3 and was approved in second line

1089
01:05:53.784 --> 01:05:55.064
small cell lung cancer.

1090
01:05:57.724 --> 01:06:01.644
For the rest of my presentation, I'll tell you about some of the challenges around

1091
01:06:01.684 --> 01:06:05.644
getting T-cell engagers approved in solid tumors and some of the

1092
01:06:05.684 --> 01:06:09.414
approaches we think we can take to try to overcome those

1093
01:06:09.484 --> 01:06:12.124
obstacles.

1094
01:06:13.984 --> 01:06:17.904
So what are the key challenges for developing these

1095
01:06:17.964 --> 01:06:19.884
molecules in solid tumors?

1096
01:06:21.564 --> 01:06:25.464
Well, as you heard from Dr. Pomper, one of the most important

1097
01:06:25.664 --> 01:06:27.864
aspects is the choice of target.

1098
01:06:29.484 --> 01:06:32.904
And what we've learned with T-cell engagers is they're incredibly

1099
01:06:32.984 --> 01:06:33.564
potent.

1100
01:06:34.444 --> 01:06:38.124
So any normal tissue expression results in

1101
01:06:38.184 --> 01:06:42.084
off-tumor activity, which can lead to toxicity

1102
01:06:42.404 --> 01:06:46.224
and safety issues. And so the selection of the target

1103
01:06:46.284 --> 01:06:46.744
is really

1104
01:06:46.804 --> 01:06:50.934
paramount.Target

1105
01:06:51.014 --> 01:06:54.914
heterogeneity is also an issue. You obviously want your target to

1106
01:06:54.934 --> 01:06:58.874
be expressed on as many cells as possible within the tumor, so

1107
01:06:58.944 --> 01:07:02.774
that you result in durable responses and

1108
01:07:02.814 --> 01:07:04.454
resistance cannot develop.

1109
01:07:06.874 --> 01:07:10.854
Another significant challenge for solid tumors is what we refer

1110
01:07:10.974 --> 01:07:14.474
to as the immunosuppressive tumor microenvironment.

1111
01:07:16.174 --> 01:07:20.054
What this means is that other cells within the

1112
01:07:20.074 --> 01:07:24.004
tumor microenvironment can prevent the T cells from working,

1113
01:07:24.034 --> 01:07:26.744
such as myeloid cells or other T cells.

1114
01:07:27.134 --> 01:07:30.114
And so we need approaches to try to mitigate the

1115
01:07:30.134 --> 01:07:32.094
immunosuppressive environment.

1116
01:07:33.894 --> 01:07:37.734
And finally, you obviously want your therapeutic to get into the tumor and

1117
01:07:37.794 --> 01:07:40.874
penetrate well, otherwise it's not going to work.

1118
01:07:41.194 --> 01:07:44.614
And so biodistribution is a key factor.

1119
01:07:48.254 --> 01:07:52.083
So we now need very specific and engineered molecules to try

1120
01:07:52.194 --> 01:07:56.014
to address some of those challenges, and I've listed some of them on

1121
01:07:56.074 --> 01:07:56.654
this slide.

1122
01:07:57.494 --> 01:08:01.294
We've been working on half-life extended formats so that we

1123
01:08:01.334 --> 01:08:05.234
can deliver intermittent dosing, which is much more convenient for the

1124
01:08:05.274 --> 01:08:05.954
patients.

1125
01:08:08.334 --> 01:08:12.074
Blinatumomab, when it was first developed, was

1126
01:08:12.154 --> 01:08:14.824
administered by continuous IV infusion.

1127
01:08:15.814 --> 01:08:19.594
And although it works well, we would like to have therapies that we could

1128
01:08:19.605 --> 01:08:23.164
deliver every week or every other week, so it's much more

1129
01:08:23.195 --> 01:08:26.674
convenient for the patient. We've been

1130
01:08:26.735 --> 01:08:30.594
working on approaches to mitigate the tumor microenvironment.

1131
01:08:31.605 --> 01:08:35.195
Those are approaches that we can use for T cell co-stimulation

1132
01:08:35.574 --> 01:08:39.434
or combination approaches, and I'll give you a couple of examples

1133
01:08:39.494 --> 01:08:41.374
of that later in my presentation.

1134
01:08:43.254 --> 01:08:46.655
Finally, we believe that avidity based or dual targeting

1135
01:08:46.695 --> 01:08:50.494
approaches is going to help us drive selectivity for tumors

1136
01:08:50.754 --> 01:08:52.494
and increase the therapeutic window.

1137
01:08:57.294 --> 01:08:59.735
So first let me tell you the story of Talatamab.

1138
01:09:01.674 --> 01:09:04.864
Talatamab is a T cell engager that targets DLL3.

1139
01:09:06.445 --> 01:09:10.344
And DLL3 has the ideal expression profile for

1140
01:09:10.344 --> 01:09:11.704
a T cell engager.

1141
01:09:13.254 --> 01:09:17.184
You can see on the left-hand side of the slide, the red dots

1142
01:09:17.254 --> 01:09:20.894
here, they represent patient samples, and they're all

1143
01:09:20.934 --> 01:09:23.284
patient samples from small cell lung cancer.

1144
01:09:23.744 --> 01:09:26.084
And what you're looking at is RNA expression data.

1145
01:09:27.155 --> 01:09:30.414
And so most patient samples express

1146
01:09:30.454 --> 01:09:31.275
DLL3.

1147
01:09:32.155 --> 01:09:34.275
It's between 80% and 90%.

1148
01:09:35.714 --> 01:09:39.424
But importantly, it's the blue squares that you have to pay

1149
01:09:39.474 --> 01:09:43.235
attention to. And the blue squares represent the normal

1150
01:09:43.294 --> 01:09:46.355
tissue expression across a panel of tissues.

1151
01:09:47.134 --> 01:09:50.174
And you can see there's very little expression of

1152
01:09:50.214 --> 01:09:52.574
DLL3 in normal tissues.

1153
01:09:54.174 --> 01:09:57.914
And we went on to do a lot of work to show that actually,

1154
01:09:57.994 --> 01:10:01.734
even that small amount of expression of DLL3 is

1155
01:10:01.744 --> 01:10:03.894
not expressed on the cell surface.

1156
01:10:04.334 --> 01:10:08.294
It's actually expressed in the Golgi, and so it's not accessible to a

1157
01:10:08.334 --> 01:10:09.294
T cell engager.

1158
01:10:11.774 --> 01:10:13.254
And so given this profile,

1159
01:10:14.114 --> 01:10:17.834
we designed the molecule on the right-hand side of the slide that's now known as

1160
01:10:17.854 --> 01:10:18.574
Talatamab.

1161
01:10:19.494 --> 01:10:23.074
It has potent binding to CD3 and very potent

1162
01:10:23.134 --> 01:10:27.114
binding to DLL3. Those are the two arms I talked about

1163
01:10:27.154 --> 01:10:30.934
earlier. And importantly, we've added a silent FC

1164
01:10:30.954 --> 01:10:34.454
domain to give us the extended half-life to allow us

1165
01:10:34.534 --> 01:10:36.214
intermittent dosing in the clinic.

1166
01:10:38.554 --> 01:10:42.434
This molecule has very potent activity on cells,

1167
01:10:43.094 --> 01:10:45.454
and some of that data is shown in the next slide.

1168
01:10:46.974 --> 01:10:50.614
On the right-hand side, you could see the cytotoxicity assay and a

1169
01:10:50.634 --> 01:10:53.854
cell-based assay. And in the top panel, you see the

1170
01:10:53.894 --> 01:10:56.834
activity in cells that express DLL3.

1171
01:10:57.574 --> 01:11:01.494
And very importantly, you see no activity when the

1172
01:11:01.514 --> 01:11:03.874
cells do not express DLL3.

1173
01:11:06.234 --> 01:11:09.974
On the left-hand side, you can see very potent T cell activation

1174
01:11:10.114 --> 01:11:14.014
and cytokine production, very much in line with that mechanism that

1175
01:11:14.114 --> 01:11:16.114
I described for a T cell engager.

1176
01:11:19.094 --> 01:11:22.694
Talatamab also has very compelling activity in

1177
01:11:22.774 --> 01:11:24.074
preclinical models.

1178
01:11:25.194 --> 01:11:28.934
In this primary small cell lung cancer model, weekly dosing of

1179
01:11:28.974 --> 01:11:32.834
Talatamab almost completely eradicated the tumors.

1180
01:11:34.654 --> 01:11:38.194
And on the right-hand side, we're looking at a liver metastasis model.

1181
01:11:38.734 --> 01:11:40.954
Again, treatment with Talatamab.

1182
01:11:41.454 --> 01:11:45.414
You can see in the liver sections below, there are almost no

1183
01:11:45.494 --> 01:11:47.274
metastases in this model.

1184
01:11:49.234 --> 01:11:51.894
And so together, these data and others

1185
01:11:53.034 --> 01:11:56.514
gave us the conviction that we should move Talatamab into clinical

1186
01:11:56.614 --> 01:11:57.134
testing.

1187
01:12:00.074 --> 01:12:03.134
And these data were published towards the end of last year.

1188
01:12:03.834 --> 01:12:05.774
This is the DELPHI-304,

1189
01:12:07.354 --> 01:12:11.194
Phase 3 study that led to the approval of Talatamab in

1190
01:12:11.274 --> 01:12:14.414
extensive stage second line small cell lung cancer.

1191
01:12:17.434 --> 01:12:20.854
The overall survival is shown for Talatamab in

1192
01:12:20.894 --> 01:12:24.654
turquoise. The median OS was 13.6

1193
01:12:24.774 --> 01:12:28.314
months, and the standard of care chemotherapy was

1194
01:12:28.534 --> 01:12:29.454
8.3 months.

1195
01:12:30.514 --> 01:12:34.374
So significant activity as monotherapy for Talatamab,

1196
01:12:34.974 --> 01:12:38.794
and really wonderful news that it's approved for patients with small cell lung

1197
01:12:38.854 --> 01:12:39.234
cancer.

1198
01:12:43.354 --> 01:12:47.314
Of course, following the framework of blinatumomab, we want

1199
01:12:47.374 --> 01:12:51.294
to move Talatamab into the frontline setting of small cell lung

1200
01:12:51.374 --> 01:12:55.262
cancer.And these data were recently published

1201
01:12:55.302 --> 01:12:58.322
where we've combined taladimab now with an anti

1202
01:12:58.482 --> 01:12:59.972
PD-L1 antibody.

1203
01:13:01.422 --> 01:13:04.932
We had fairly compelling preclinical data that treatment with

1204
01:13:04.942 --> 01:13:06.722
taladimab upregulated

1205
01:13:08.422 --> 01:13:12.272
PD-L1. And so there was strong scientific rationale for doing

1206
01:13:12.322 --> 01:13:13.782
this combination in the clinic.

1207
01:13:15.832 --> 01:13:17.622
This is now in the frontline setting.

1208
01:13:17.662 --> 01:13:21.622
This is a Phase 1b trial. And now you can see

1209
01:13:21.662 --> 01:13:24.502
it in red is treatment with atezolizumab.

1210
01:13:25.002 --> 01:13:27.822
Treatment in green is taladimab with durvalumab.

1211
01:13:28.382 --> 01:13:32.082
And finally, the blue line represents treatment with either of these

1212
01:13:32.142 --> 01:13:34.162
anti PD-L1 therapies.

1213
01:13:35.462 --> 01:13:38.602
And now the median OS in the frontline setting is up to

1214
01:13:38.762 --> 01:13:40.342
25.3 months.

1215
01:13:41.902 --> 01:13:45.862
And importantly, these patients had a very manageable

1216
01:13:46.042 --> 01:13:47.002
safety profile.

1217
01:13:48.462 --> 01:13:52.322
And so these data have given us conviction to move taladimab

1218
01:13:52.342 --> 01:13:56.242
in combination with an anti PD-L1 therapy into Phase

1219
01:13:56.342 --> 01:13:57.702
III clinical trials.

1220
01:13:58.742 --> 01:14:00.962
Very impressive clinical data.

1221
01:14:03.602 --> 01:14:06.522
But that's not all from the combination point of view.

1222
01:14:08.382 --> 01:14:12.322
As you heard about from my colleagues earlier today, we think combination

1223
01:14:12.362 --> 01:14:16.212
strategies are going to allow us to treat more patients and

1224
01:14:16.302 --> 01:14:19.622
have more durable responses. And I'm showing two

1225
01:14:19.742 --> 01:14:23.602
examples here. One is from an antibody drug conjugate that we just

1226
01:14:23.662 --> 01:14:26.812
heard about. The target here is B7H3.

1227
01:14:27.762 --> 01:14:31.412
And when we've combined taladimab with the antibody drug conjugate,

1228
01:14:31.682 --> 01:14:34.182
we see very compelling preclinical activity.

1229
01:14:35.112 --> 01:14:38.962
And we believe that targeting these orthogonal mechanisms will

1230
01:14:39.022 --> 01:14:40.802
lead to improved outcomes.

1231
01:14:42.502 --> 01:14:46.062
On the left-hand side, you're looking at combination with an IL-2

1232
01:14:46.102 --> 01:14:46.702
mutine.

1233
01:14:47.962 --> 01:14:50.422
This molecule, we believe, will overcome some of those

1234
01:14:50.522 --> 01:14:52.162
immunosuppressive

1235
01:14:53.322 --> 01:14:55.882
properties of solid tumors that we talked about.

