1417
01:26:41.160 --> 01:26:44.790
So when you think about TIL therapy, what is required

1418
01:26:45.080 --> 01:26:48.680
first is a surgical resection of a metastatic

1419
01:26:48.820 --> 01:26:49.160
lesion.

1420
01:26:49.980 --> 01:26:53.340
And then that material is enzymatically digested

1421
01:26:53.920 --> 01:26:57.840
or fragmented, and then those fragments or cell

1422
01:26:57.920 --> 01:27:01.840
suspensions are cultured in the presence of very high

1423
01:27:02.000 --> 01:27:05.560
concentrations of interleukin-2, up to 6,000 units per

1424
01:27:05.620 --> 01:27:08.700
milliliter. And upon initial TIL growth,

1425
01:27:09.660 --> 01:27:13.540
the cells are then further very aspecifically expanded in the

1426
01:27:13.560 --> 01:27:16.210
presence of soluble CD3 antibody,

1427
01:27:16.840 --> 01:27:20.740
irradiated allogeneic feeder cells, and again, high doses of

1428
01:27:20.900 --> 01:27:24.780
interleukin-2 to really amount to a product which consists

1429
01:27:24.860 --> 01:27:27.780
solely of CD3 positive cells in the billions.

1430
01:27:29.200 --> 01:27:31.900
And meanwhile, the patient is admitted to the hospital

1431
01:27:32.880 --> 01:27:36.200
to receive lymph depleting

1432
01:27:36.360 --> 01:27:40.220
chemotherapy consisting of cyclophosphamide and fludarabine, quite high

1433
01:27:40.280 --> 01:27:41.700
doses, followed by then

1434
01:27:42.660 --> 01:27:46.429
TIL infusion, and after TIL infusion, a couple of doses

1435
01:27:46.480 --> 01:27:48.860
of high-dose interleukin-2.

1436
01:27:51.120 --> 01:27:54.980
Around 2012, we knew that coming from phase one and phase

1437
01:27:55.080 --> 01:27:58.610
two studies in multiple institutions, that very consistently

1438
01:27:58.960 --> 01:28:02.620
TIL showed clinical efficacy in patients with metastatic

1439
01:28:02.640 --> 01:28:06.580
melanoma, and it was, of course, at the time that also checkpoint inhibition became

1440
01:28:06.640 --> 01:28:07.119
available.

1441
01:28:08.120 --> 01:28:11.600
So at that time, we had an important question to answer.

1442
01:28:12.060 --> 01:28:15.220
Would it be possible to estimate a true value of TIL

1443
01:28:15.760 --> 01:28:19.560
therapy by comparing it head-to-head with the standard of care?

1444
01:28:20.860 --> 01:28:23.260
And at the time, there was not so much interest

1445
01:28:24.760 --> 01:28:27.680
by pharma for TIL. Of course, that changed over time.

1446
01:28:28.820 --> 01:28:32.580
And therefore, we thought that a randomized control trial should be done in an

1447
01:28:32.620 --> 01:28:36.400
academic setting. And if that trial would be positive, would

1448
01:28:36.460 --> 01:28:40.260
TIL become available as a new standard of care treatment?

1449
01:28:42.060 --> 01:28:44.840
So I teamed up with Inge Riis-Faine

1450
01:28:46.460 --> 01:28:50.180
from Copenhagen in Denmark, who was also running trials

1451
01:28:50.780 --> 01:28:53.960
with TIL in patients with melanoma, and together we

1452
01:28:53.980 --> 01:28:56.360
designed a randomized controlled phase three trial.

1453
01:28:57.880 --> 01:29:01.820
This was 2014, and at that time, there was already

1454
01:29:01.860 --> 01:29:05.840
very interesting data, very promising data from nivolumab and pembrolizumab as

1455
01:29:05.900 --> 01:29:08.480
first-line treatment for patients with metastatic melanoma.

1456
01:29:08.560 --> 01:29:12.460
So we allowed one prior line of treatment in the study.

1457
01:29:12.500 --> 01:29:16.340
And in fact, almost 90% of the patients treated in

1458
01:29:16.380 --> 01:29:19.940
this randomized controlled phase three trial had progressed on prior

1459
01:29:19.950 --> 01:29:23.860
anti-PD-1 treatment. So 168 patients were

1460
01:29:23.900 --> 01:29:27.500
randomized to receive either TIL, exactly the way I described to you

1461
01:29:27.519 --> 01:29:31.500
before, or as a standard of care, ipilimumab at a

1462
01:29:31.519 --> 01:29:35.440
dose of three milligrams per kilogram every three weeks for a maximum of

1463
01:29:35.480 --> 01:29:37.920
four doses. And then those patients would be followed.

1464
01:29:39.170 --> 01:29:42.780
The primary endpoint of the study was progression-free survival according to RECIST

1465
01:29:42.940 --> 01:29:46.599
1.1 in the intention-to-treat population.

1466
01:29:46.760 --> 01:29:50.660
We showed that the primary endpoint was met with a

1467
01:29:50.680 --> 01:29:54.260
clear improvement in progression-free survival for patients

1468
01:29:54.300 --> 01:29:57.590
treated with TIL compared to ipilimumab.

1469
01:29:57.860 --> 01:30:01.100
And this was statistically significant but also highly clinically relevant.

1470
01:30:03.340 --> 01:30:06.720
Also, a secondary endpoint, best objective response rate, was much better for

1471
01:30:06.760 --> 01:30:09.300
patients treated with TIL, 49%

1472
01:30:10.240 --> 01:30:14.040
overall response rate and 20% of these patients having a complete response.

1473
01:30:14.880 --> 01:30:15.750
In terms of safety,

1474
01:30:16.650 --> 01:30:20.040
this was mostly coming from the lymph depleting

1475
01:30:20.080 --> 01:30:23.940
